cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses attacks on stream and block ciphers, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the use of time-memory-data trade-off attacks, which is a technique that involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of attacks on ciphers and compares them to exhaustive search, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the analysis and breaking of cryptographic systems, which can be considered as a control problem. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may involve the implementation and testing of the attacks on ciphers, which can be considered as a software engineering task.
